---

<section
  class="grid grid-cols-3 gap-3 py-10 border-t border-[var(--border)] max-md:grid-cols-1"
>
  <div
    class="p-4 bg-[var(--surface)] border border-[var(--border)] rounded-md"
  >
    <h3 class="text-[13px] font-bold mb-1.5 text-[var(--bright)]">
      Live state, not pixels
    </h3>
    <p class="text-[13px] leading-relaxed text-[var(--dim)]">
      blit tracks the full parsed terminal grid and sends only what changed —
      LZ4-compressed binary diffs. The browser gets real structured data: select
      text, resize freely, type into it.
    </p>
  </div>
  <div
    class="p-4 bg-[var(--surface)] border border-[var(--border)] rounded-md"
  >
    <h3 class="text-[13px] font-bold mb-1.5 text-[var(--bright)]">
      Share with one command
    </h3>
    <p class="text-[13px] leading-relaxed text-[var(--dim)]">
      <code
        class="text-xs bg-[var(--code-bg)] px-1 py-0.5 rounded border border-[var(--border)]"
        >blit share</code
      > prints a URL. Open it anywhere. WebRTC punches through NATs — no SSH keys,
      no port forwarding, no tunnels. Full input for pair programming or AI agents.
    </p>
  </div>
  <div
    class="p-4 bg-[var(--surface)] border border-[var(--border)] rounded-md"
  >
    <h3 class="text-[13px] font-bold mb-1.5 text-[var(--bright)]">
      Terminals as an API
    </h3>
    <p class="text-[13px] leading-relaxed text-[var(--dim)]">
      Non-interactive CLI for scripts and LLMs. <code
        class="text-xs bg-[var(--code-bg)] px-1 py-0.5 rounded border border-[var(--border)]"
        >blit start</code
      >, <code
        class="text-xs bg-[var(--code-bg)] px-1 py-0.5 rounded border border-[var(--border)]"
        >show</code
      >, <code
        class="text-xs bg-[var(--code-bg)] px-1 py-0.5 rounded border border-[var(--border)]"
        >send</code
      >, <code
        class="text-xs bg-[var(--code-bg)] px-1 py-0.5 rounded border border-[var(--border)]"
        >wait --pattern</code
      >. Plain text out, zero exit on success. No screen-scraping.
    </p>
  </div>
</section>
